==English==
===Etymology===
After [[w:Edwin Hubble|Edwin Powell Hubble]], American astronomer
===Noun===
'''Hubble constant'''
#{{astronomy}} a [[number]] the expresses the [[rate]] of [[expansion]] of the [[universe]]; the [[velocity]] at which a distant object is [[receeding]] from the [[Earth]] divided by its [[distance]]; its [[reciprocal]] gives the [[age]] of the universe
===Alternative spellings===
*[[Hubble's constant]]
===Related terms===
*[[Hubble law]]
